1
00:00:03,148 --> 00:00:04,740
<i>Almost half of this country</i>

2
00:00:04,801 --> 00:00:06,910
<i>doesn't go to the doctor
when they should.</i>

3
00:00:07,191 --> 00:00:08,652
<i>Many don't have access,</i>

4
00:00:09,027 --> 00:00:11,558
<i>but a lot of others,
they just don't want to.</i>

5
00:00:12,433 --> 00:00:15,215
<i>♪ The end's in sight now ♪</i>

6
00:00:15,310 --> 00:00:16,340
<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

7
00:00:16,428 --> 00:00:18,699
<i>♪ No one left behind ♪</i>

8
00:00:19,442 --> 00:00:20,675
<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

9
00:00:20,763 --> 00:00:22,433
<i>♪ And you don't ask why ♪</i>

10
00:00:23,606 --> 00:00:24,653
<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

11
00:00:24,741 --> 00:00:26,694
<i>♪ We all are safe here ♪</i>

12
00:00:26,786 --> 00:00:29,613
<i>Because they don't believe
anything is actually wrong.</i>

13
00:00:29,701 --> 00:00:31,785
Illuminating exchange.

14
00:00:32,168 --> 00:00:34,410
Any Maggie sightings
today?

15
00:00:35,223 --> 00:00:37,332
Uh, well, I sent Zola up
with food.

16
00:00:37,420 --> 00:00:38,753
She refused it.

17
00:00:38,845 --> 00:00:39,957
We'll know when to push.

18
00:00:40,045 --> 00:00:42,088
I wish I could just
stay in bed.

19
00:00:42,362 --> 00:00:43,735
I actually might.

20
00:00:44,238 --> 00:00:45,371
I might go back to bed.

21
00:00:45,458 --> 00:00:46,595
No.
Not doing that.

22
00:00:46,683 --> 00:00:48,986
I'm gonna be brave.
I'm gonna face this.

23
00:00:49,223 --> 00:00:50,926
First chance I get.
Rigorous honesty.

24
00:00:51,013 --> 00:00:52,801
What are we
talking about?

25
00:00:52,933 --> 00:00:55,266
<i>♪ In the spotlight ♪</i>

26
00:00:55,353 --> 00:00:57,216
<i>♪ Stand up, cuz,
you're in the spotlight ♪</i>

27
00:00:57,303 --> 00:00:59,466
Um... may I?

28
00:00:59,554 --> 00:01:01,062
<i>♪ You were made for it ♪</i>

29
00:01:01,150 --> 00:01:02,943
- I'm Cormac Hayes.
- Amelia.

30
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:05,676
And... God, yes.

31
00:01:05,764 --> 00:01:07,637
I-I mean... yes,
that is...

32
00:01:07,941 --> 00:01:09,158
very helpful.

33
00:01:09,263 --> 00:01:11,466
<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

34
00:01:11,605 --> 00:01:12,699
Dr. Grey.

35
00:01:12,787 --> 00:01:13,814
Morning.

36
00:01:13,902 --> 00:01:15,021
Hello.

37
00:01:16,205 --> 00:01:17,636
Coffee?

38
00:01:17,723 --> 00:01:18,921
<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

39
00:01:19,009 --> 00:01:20,197
Me?

40
00:01:20,417 --> 00:01:22,150
- Yeah.
- No, I'm good. Thanks.

41
00:01:22,246 --> 00:01:23,634
Very good coffee
for a hospital.

42
00:01:23,722 --> 00:01:24,845
Or for anywhere,
really.

43
00:01:24,933 --> 00:01:27,627
Yeah, Seattle is kind of known
for its coffee.

44
00:01:27,715 --> 00:01:29,721
It's, uh, better
at the cart outside.

45
00:01:29,871 --> 00:01:31,001
Right.

46
00:01:32,212 --> 00:01:34,150
Noted and appreciated.

47
00:01:37,644 --> 00:01:40,330
That is
a very well-wrapped gift.

48
00:01:40,473 --> 00:01:42,830
<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

49
00:01:42,925 --> 00:01:43,968
<i>♪ La, la, la ♪</i>

50
00:01:44,183 --> 00:01:46,127
<i>♪ La, la, la ♪
Hey!</i>

51
00:01:46,407 --> 00:01:48,681
Plastics needs to look
at the facial lac in bed 6.

52
00:01:48,769 --> 00:01:51,478
MVC victim in trauma 2
is about to go up to CT.

53
00:01:51,566 --> 00:01:55,603
I've got ortho on the way
to assess the girl in bed 4.

54
00:01:55,794 --> 00:01:57,275
- Dr. Altman?
- Yeah?

55
00:01:57,486 --> 00:01:59,149
Uh,
what are you doing?

56
00:01:59,691 --> 00:02:01,387
- I lost my engagement ring.
- Oh.

57
00:02:01,511 --> 00:02:03,043
Oh, no!

58
00:02:03,138 --> 00:02:04,185
Isn't that, like,
some sort of...

59
00:02:04,272 --> 00:02:05,582
- Hunt family heirloom?
- Yes.

60
00:02:05,709 --> 00:02:09,129
Ugh. That's why I never take
mine off except for surgery.

61
00:02:10,093 --> 00:02:11,629
I'll...
I'll keep an eye out.

62
00:02:24,303 --> 00:02:26,348
You told me to take
some time to think,

63
00:02:26,436 --> 00:02:29,539
which I didn't like, because
two people who are together

64
00:02:29,627 --> 00:02:31,418
should think through things
together.

65
00:02:33,098 --> 00:02:36,895
Look, I-I did a routine lap appy
on a patient,

66
00:02:36,983 --> 00:02:38,238
and she's
not getting better.

67
00:02:38,503 --> 00:02:40,454
She's post op day three,
she's fevering,

68
00:02:40,542 --> 00:02:41,502
she's got
a high white count.

69
00:02:41,590 --> 00:02:43,785
I did a sepsis workup.
It all came back negative.

70
00:02:43,978 --> 00:02:46,167
Okay, well,
I'll think on it.

71
00:02:46,301 --> 00:02:48,527
In the meantime,
I think you should fill Bailey in.

72
00:02:49,379 --> 00:02:50,379
Yeah.

73
00:02:52,941 --> 00:02:55,021
<i>Speaking Italian...</i>

74
00:02:56,407 --> 00:02:57,487
Hey.

75
00:02:58,900 --> 00:03:01,745
You know, I didn't dump you,
Meredith, so...

76
00:03:02,053 --> 00:03:03,331
you don't have to miss me.

77
00:03:08,917 --> 00:03:09,970
Coffee smells good.

78
00:03:11,168 --> 00:03:12,355
You okay?

79
00:03:13,025 --> 00:03:14,417
Coffee smells bad?

80
00:03:15,183 --> 00:03:17,284
Uh... baby's kicking?

81
00:03:17,926 --> 00:03:19,259
You woke up this morning

82
00:03:19,347 --> 00:03:21,745
with a deep knowing
I'm not fatherhood material?

83
00:03:22,644 --> 00:03:23,980
Link, I hate this.

84
00:03:24,068 --> 00:03:26,768
I... I'm not sure
that I have the ability

85
00:03:26,856 --> 00:03:28,323
to convey
how much I hate this.

86
00:03:29,723 --> 00:03:31,097
But I promise you,

87
00:03:31,238 --> 00:03:33,316
no blood test can change
the way I feel about you.

88
00:03:33,404 --> 00:03:35,097
It's just a matter
of some cells.

89
00:03:36,464 --> 00:03:38,716
I... still have no idea
what you're talking about.

90
00:03:40,103 --> 00:03:42,846
I am more pregnant
than I thought.

91
00:03:43,597 --> 00:03:44,745
Okay...?

92
00:03:45,372 --> 00:03:48,652
Which means there is a chance
that you aren't the father.

93
00:03:54,216 --> 00:03:55,830
It took me a few days
to work up the nerve

94
00:03:55,917 --> 00:03:57,143
to tell you.

95
00:04:02,526 --> 00:04:04,149
We're talking about Owen,
right?

96
00:04:04,393 --> 00:04:05,659
Yeah.

97
00:04:06,379 --> 00:04:07,379
Does he know?

98
00:04:08,667 --> 00:04:10,425
I'm talking to you first.

99
00:04:11,386 --> 00:04:13,259
Because I don't need
a paternity test

100
00:04:13,347 --> 00:04:15,245
to know that I want
to be with you.

101
00:04:16,097 --> 00:04:18,777
I love what we have.

102
00:04:19,347 --> 00:04:24,058
I love your kindness
and I love our ease

103
00:04:24,146 --> 00:04:28,222
and I love that you
make me laugh all the time

104
00:04:28,310 --> 00:04:30,800
and you have yet
to make me cry.

105
00:04:32,581 --> 00:04:34,120
I'm in love with you,
Link.

106
00:04:35,518 --> 00:04:37,503
And the genetics
don't matter to me.

107
00:04:38,394 --> 00:04:40,386
But I have been sitting with it
for a few days,

108
00:04:40,473 --> 00:04:41,803
and you haven't.

109
00:04:43,401 --> 00:04:44,738
So...

110
00:04:50,323 --> 00:04:52,026
Take some time
to think.

111
00:04:57,393 --> 00:04:58,972
Welcome back,
Dr. Bailey.

112
00:04:59,089 --> 00:05:01,511
Quick update on the residents...
We've removed Simms' trach

113
00:05:01,599 --> 00:05:03,011
and started him
on a soft diet.

114
00:05:03,099 --> 00:05:04,363
Helm's chest tubes
were removed,

115
00:05:04,451 --> 00:05:06,165
and she actually took
a couple steps today with PT.

116
00:05:06,252 --> 00:05:07,691
Parker left
for neural rehab,

117
00:05:07,779 --> 00:05:09,903
and Schmitt was discharged with
a couple weeks' medical leave.

118
00:05:09,990 --> 00:05:11,443
Sounds like
you're pretty busy.

119
00:05:11,552 --> 00:05:12,863
Yeah, I am.

120
00:05:13,217 --> 00:05:15,097
So, why are you
glued to my side right now?

121
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:17,613
I was hoping you could weigh in
on an appy patient of mine.

122
00:05:17,701 --> 00:05:18,784
She's post-op day three.

123
00:05:18,872 --> 00:05:20,246
She's been giving me
more questions than answers.

124
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:21,488
Mm. Lead the way.

125
00:05:21,576 --> 00:05:23,821
Dr. Bailey. A funny thing
happened yesterday.

126
00:05:23,909 --> 00:05:25,386
I came to your office
for a budget meeting,

127
00:05:25,473 --> 00:05:26,386
and you weren't there.

128
00:05:26,474 --> 00:05:27,777
I took some personal days.

129
00:05:27,865 --> 00:05:30,040
Even when half your residents
are on bedpans?

130
00:05:30,128 --> 00:05:30,886
That's great timing,
Chief.

131
00:05:30,974 --> 00:05:32,434
I-I asked
some of the other departments

132
00:05:32,521 --> 00:05:33,605
to lend us
some residents

133
00:05:33,693 --> 00:05:35,181
for surgical floor
and ICU coverage.

134
00:05:35,269 --> 00:05:36,354
- They were happy to help.
- Even so,

135
00:05:36,441 --> 00:05:37,660
next time
you want to take a vacay,

136
00:05:37,747 --> 00:05:40,113
run it up the flagpole,
as in me.

137
00:05:41,831 --> 00:05:43,323
D... Uh, thank you.

138
00:05:43,411 --> 00:05:44,798
- Mom?
- Yes, honey?

139
00:05:44,886 --> 00:05:46,253
Can I be done?

140
00:05:46,341 --> 00:05:49,284
Just a few more times, sweet girl.
You got this.

141
00:05:50,067 --> 00:05:51,641
Oh. It's her therapy.

142
00:05:51,729 --> 00:05:52,941
I know it looks nuts.

143
00:05:53,029 --> 00:05:55,269
Mei I. was adopted
from an orphanage,

144
00:05:55,357 --> 00:05:58,165
and she was recently diagnosed
with attachment disorder,

145
00:05:58,253 --> 00:05:59,598
so we've been doing
this crawling therapy

146
00:05:59,685 --> 00:06:01,433
because it's supposed to
rewire her brain.

147
00:06:01,521 --> 00:06:03,340
But you got to do it every day,
and you got to be

148
00:06:03,427 --> 00:06:05,525
super consistent with it
every day.

149
00:06:05,613 --> 00:06:07,800
Hi.
I'm her sister.

150
00:06:07,910 --> 00:06:09,949
It was an appendectomy.
You said it went without a hitch.

151
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:11,321
So, um,
why are we still here?

152
00:06:11,409 --> 00:06:12,486
Take this. Please.

153
00:06:12,573 --> 00:06:13,981
She's been spiking fevers
every night.

154
00:06:14,069 --> 00:06:15,514
Yeah, I know.
I'm asking why.

155
00:06:15,602 --> 00:06:16,629
- And I have brought our
- Mom? Yes, sweetheart.

156
00:06:16,717 --> 00:06:18,301
chief of surgery to help
determine that.

157
00:06:18,411 --> 00:06:20,169
- Uh, here. You, too, sweetheart.
- Here.

158
00:06:20,256 --> 00:06:21,549
Dr. Bailey,
Suzanne Britland.

159
00:06:21,644 --> 00:06:23,191
- Hi.
- Good morning.

160
00:06:23,279 --> 00:06:24,489
Ms. Britland,
how are you feeling?

161
00:06:24,576 --> 00:06:26,456
- She has a sore throat.
- He has a sore throat.

162
00:06:26,566 --> 00:06:28,534
It's just a little sore.

163
00:06:29,339 --> 00:06:30,886
I'm probably
just getting a cold.

164
00:06:30,974 --> 00:06:32,467
It could still be
from the intubation.

165
00:06:32,555 --> 00:06:33,402
Could be.

166
00:06:33,490 --> 00:06:35,402
I know that the answer
is probably "no,"

167
00:06:35,490 --> 00:06:37,454
but is there any way
you could just send me home

168
00:06:37,542 --> 00:06:38,596
with some antibiotics?

169
00:06:38,683 --> 00:06:41,089
Not until you've been fever-free
for 24 hours. I'm sorry.

170
00:06:41,177 --> 00:06:43,341
Oh, it's just, the kids are
missing so much school.

171
00:06:43,444 --> 00:06:44,857
Well, I can take them
to school.

172
00:06:44,945 --> 00:06:45,945
- No!
- No!

173
00:06:47,362 --> 00:06:48,386
Okay.

174
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:49,839
It's okay.

175
00:06:52,676 --> 00:06:53,956
Their dad died
last year.

176
00:06:55,035 --> 00:06:57,698
He had a migraine,
and then when it got really bad,

177
00:06:57,786 --> 00:07:00,548
we took him to the ER,
and the doctors told us

178
00:07:00,636 --> 00:07:02,337
we could go home
and he would be fine,

179
00:07:02,425 --> 00:07:03,472
and then...

180
00:07:05,481 --> 00:07:06,981
..he very much wasn't.

181
00:07:08,904 --> 00:07:10,527
We are running
a fresh set of labs,

182
00:07:10,615 --> 00:07:12,245
and we hope
to know more soon.

183
00:07:12,729 --> 00:07:13,823
Okay.

184
00:07:24,083 --> 00:07:25,286
Dr. Grey.

185
00:07:25,550 --> 00:07:26,550
Hey.

186
00:07:27,199 --> 00:07:29,402
So,
elephant in the room...

187
00:07:29,832 --> 00:07:32,253
I'm not sure what Cristina
said to you, but...

188
00:07:32,352 --> 00:07:33,753
- Who?
- ..I...

189
00:07:34,143 --> 00:07:35,878
..never mind.
Who did you say?

190
00:07:35,995 --> 00:07:37,089
Never mind.

191
00:07:37,823 --> 00:07:38,966
Are you coming
to the pit?

192
00:07:39,089 --> 00:07:40,698
- What?
- The pit.

193
00:07:40,869 --> 00:07:42,643
- The what?
- The ER.

194
00:07:42,853 --> 00:07:44,292
You call the ER
"the pit"?

195
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:45,675
- Yeah.
- Why?

196
00:07:46,104 --> 00:07:47,331
I don't know.

197
00:07:51,581 --> 00:07:53,363
Oh, my God! Kai?

198
00:07:53,636 --> 00:07:54,527
What's happening
to him?

199
00:07:54,615 --> 00:07:55,938
What do we know?
17 years old.

200
00:07:56,026 --> 00:07:57,216
He came in with
shortness of breath.

201
00:07:57,303 --> 00:07:58,831
He just started
coughing up blood.

202
00:07:58,919 --> 00:08:00,739
- We need suction and an intubation tray.
- Help him, please!

203
00:08:00,826 --> 00:08:03,470
We should set up for
an emergency bronchoscopy also.

