208
00:08:39,593 --> 00:08:40,901
You can't see inside.

209
00:08:41,723 --> 00:08:42,973
Was I wrong?

210
00:08:45,222 --> 00:08:46,800
What are you doing here?

211
00:08:46,942 --> 00:08:49,136
Um, well, I was thinking
about taking you to breakfast,

212
00:08:49,224 --> 00:08:50,925
but, uh,
now that I see you,

213
00:08:51,013 --> 00:08:54,151
um, I'm thinking eat in.

214
00:08:54,745 --> 00:08:56,058
How's pancakes sound?

215
00:08:56,626 --> 00:08:57,626
What?

216
00:08:58,366 --> 00:08:59,917
I didn't know
you could cook.

217
00:09:00,893 --> 00:09:02,191
Please.

218
00:09:05,206 --> 00:09:06,386
Hey!

219
00:09:06,519 --> 00:09:07,581
Hey.

220
00:09:07,693 --> 00:09:09,534
What's, uh...
What are we...

221
00:09:09,995 --> 00:09:11,922
Oh. Oh, wait.
Are you meditating?

222
00:09:12,010 --> 00:09:13,933
- I'm sorry. I can...
- No. No, I was...

223
00:09:14,274 --> 00:09:16,637
Amelia said
the baby might be Owen's.

224
00:09:16,725 --> 00:09:17,730
What?

225
00:09:17,818 --> 00:09:19,102
Somebody help me, please!

226
00:09:19,190 --> 00:09:21,845
All these blue pajamas, I can't
get any help over here?!

227
00:09:21,933 --> 00:09:23,598
- Oh, sorry. The ER's this way.
- What happened?

228
00:09:23,685 --> 00:09:26,056
We'll go get your hand fixed up,
and I promise you can punch me.

229
00:09:26,143 --> 00:09:26,886
Okay,
what happened?

230
00:09:26,974 --> 00:09:28,506
I'm trying to rush Chuck
to the ER,

231
00:09:28,594 --> 00:09:30,582
and I accidentally slammed
his hand in the cab's door.

232
00:09:30,669 --> 00:09:32,162
Wait. Why were you
rushing to the ER?

233
00:09:32,256 --> 00:09:33,419
Oh,
because of the fish.

234
00:09:35,357 --> 00:09:36,878
There's a fish
inside of there.

235
00:09:36,966 --> 00:09:39,173
What, like... like,
part of a fish or a bone or...

236
00:09:39,261 --> 00:09:40,924
No,
an entire fish, sir.

237
00:09:42,675 --> 00:09:44,306
- Okay, Link, with you...
- Later.

238
00:09:44,393 --> 00:09:45,761
Spilling blood
everywhere.

239
00:09:46,190 --> 00:09:48,675
Kai's bronchoscopy was
surprisingly clean.

240
00:09:48,763 --> 00:09:50,176
We didn't see any bleeding
in his lungs,

241
00:09:50,263 --> 00:09:51,441
just some inflammation.

242
00:09:51,529 --> 00:09:52,562
Isn't that good news?

243
00:09:52,650 --> 00:09:54,495
Not exactly.
Dr. Grey did an EGD.

244
00:09:54,583 --> 00:09:56,616
She found the source
of the bleed in his esophagus.

245
00:09:56,693 --> 00:09:58,526
We're just not sure
exactly why he's bleeding.

246
00:09:58,621 --> 00:10:00,494
Everything was normal
at practice.

247
00:10:00,878 --> 00:10:02,300
He started hacking up
like crazy.

248
00:10:02,388 --> 00:10:03,378
I mean,
Kai's never sick.

249
00:10:03,466 --> 00:10:04,790
Kai's the best
on the team.

250
00:10:04,878 --> 00:10:06,846
He's got the fastest 200
in the school's history.

