00:30:00,664 --> 00:30:02,896
just yell,
just be mad at me.

759
00:30:05,763 --> 00:30:07,056
Okay, I liked her.

760
00:30:07,183 --> 00:30:09,466
I-I-I really loved
the idea

761
00:30:09,553 --> 00:30:11,306
of finally having
one of those big families

762
00:30:11,393 --> 00:30:13,543
like I saw all my friends
growing up with

763
00:30:13,631 --> 00:30:14,381
when I was a kid,

764
00:30:14,469 --> 00:30:17,595
and I only got her for one day,
and then she was gone.

765
00:30:17,683 --> 00:30:18,982
But you...

766
00:30:20,223 --> 00:30:22,326
you lost your niece.

767
00:30:22,513 --> 00:30:24,216
And probably your brother.

768
00:30:24,325 --> 00:30:26,105
I destroyed your family,

769
00:30:26,193 --> 00:30:29,153
and they deserve to sue me
for everything that I've got.

770
00:30:34,348 --> 00:30:36,248
Why don't you
make yourself useful

771
00:30:36,614 --> 00:30:38,912
and open the flour,
would you?

772
00:30:42,643 --> 00:30:43,926
Guess I can see

773
00:30:44,013 --> 00:30:47,412
who I inherited my distaste
for sharing my emotions from.

774
00:30:48,511 --> 00:30:49,794
When, uh...

775
00:30:49,882 --> 00:30:54,037
I was only 10 years old...
when my mother died.

776
00:30:55,886 --> 00:30:58,259
I don't remember much,
you know,

777
00:30:58,409 --> 00:31:01,709
but I remember
I was temperamental sometimes.

778
00:31:01,797 --> 00:31:04,096
A "hot head," she called it.

779
00:31:04,224 --> 00:31:06,959
But she wouldn't send me
to a time-out

780
00:31:07,047 --> 00:31:10,268
or... make me sit and think
about what I've done.

781
00:31:10,379 --> 00:31:11,712
She would go
to the kitchen

782
00:31:11,900 --> 00:31:14,063
and she would make us both
some pancakes,

783
00:31:14,205 --> 00:31:16,595
and she'd say,
"Let's talk about it

784
00:31:16,683 --> 00:31:18,513
after you've had
something to eat."

785
00:31:20,379 --> 00:31:22,471
She didn't get a chance
to teach me much.

786
00:31:23,479 --> 00:31:25,370
But it's a lesson
I'll never forget.

787
00:31:30,456 --> 00:31:31,987
Ah, let's see.

788
00:31:40,737 --> 00:31:43,245
I've been doing it
over and over again.

789
00:31:43,333 --> 00:31:47,556
I've been... going over
every second of Sabi.

790
00:31:48,167 --> 00:31:51,175
I've been replaying in my mind
and just...

791
00:31:51,553 --> 00:31:53,565
wondering what
I could have done

792
00:31:53,925 --> 00:31:56,800
better, smarter...

793
00:31:57,557 --> 00:31:59,628
- faster.
- It's not on you.

794
00:32:00,463 --> 00:32:03,057
Family doesn't operate
on family, Maggie.

795
00:32:03,353 --> 00:32:04,690
I knew better.

796
00:32:04,934 --> 00:32:08,517
I put you in that OR anyway
out of desperation.

797
00:32:08,683 --> 00:32:10,081
I made a mistake.

798
00:32:11,081 --> 00:32:12,506
And now Sabi is dead.

799
00:32:12,593 --> 00:32:14,667
And you'll never
make that mistake again.

800
00:32:15,752 --> 00:32:16,995
That's what you say
to interns

801
00:32:17,083 --> 00:32:19,866
who... who have lost
their first patient, not to...

802
00:32:20,093 --> 00:32:21,682
They're human.

803
00:32:22,456 --> 00:32:24,143
And imperfect.

804
00:32:24,412 --> 00:32:25,912
Like you.

805
00:32:29,973 --> 00:32:32,534
No one has ever
had to tell me that before.

806
00:32:33,050 --> 00:32:35,120
Then let Sabi's legacy
be that.

807
00:32:35,208 --> 00:32:37,614
She taught you
what years of school

808
00:32:37,702 --> 00:32:39,064
and residency

809
00:32:39,152 --> 00:32:41,151
and countless hours
never did.

810
00:32:41,556 --> 00:32:44,503
Maggie, you have insurance
for this.

811
00:32:45,011 --> 00:32:46,401
They'll settle with Chris.

812
00:32:46,536 --> 00:32:48,081
It won't bring Sabi back,

813
00:32:48,287 --> 00:32:52,659
but he'll feel like
he's got some justice for her.

814
00:32:53,369 --> 00:32:54,893
And he needs that.

815
00:32:55,839 --> 00:32:58,466
Every surgeon I know
goes through this.

816
00:32:58,919 --> 00:33:00,965
And if you quit now,
you'll be quitting

817
00:33:01,053 --> 00:33:03,756
on all those lives
that only you can save.

818
00:33:04,085 --> 00:33:06,271
And I know
Sabi wouldn't want that.

819
00:33:10,591 --> 00:33:12,504
I wish I could've had
more time with her.

820
00:33:12,592 --> 00:33:15,693
Well, ask me
anything you want about her.

821
00:33:15,917 --> 00:33:17,701
No. Richard,
I am not gonna make you...

822
00:33:17,789 --> 00:33:20,099
No, you know, truth be told,
talking about her

823
00:33:20,187 --> 00:33:22,140
is about the only thing
I want to do right now.

824
00:33:30,013 --> 00:33:31,266
Okay,
you don't have to stay

825
00:33:31,353 --> 00:33:32,920
if you need
to check in downstairs.

826
00:33:33,246 --> 00:33:34,990
No, I'm staying.
I feel awful.

827
00:33:35,545 --> 00:33:37,238
Listen, we know
where the ring is, Teddy,

828
00:33:37,326 --> 00:33:38,676
and it's not
perforating anything.

829
00:33:38,763 --> 00:33:39,928
He's gonna be fine.

830
00:33:40,016 --> 00:33:41,600
I mean, kids do
this kind of stuff, you know?

831
00:33:41,687 --> 00:33:43,430
We see cases like this
all the time.

832
00:33:43,518 --> 00:33:45,555
I know, Owen,
but I feel awful.

833
00:33:45,643 --> 00:33:49,346
I mean, your grandmother
and your mom all wore the ring,

834
00:33:49,433 --> 00:33:51,386
and it's survived
in your family for years,

835
00:33:51,473 --> 00:33:52,842
through wars
and depressions,

836
00:33:52,930 --> 00:33:54,990
and I couldn't even
keep it for a week.

837
00:33:55,078 --> 00:33:57,201
'Cause you're tired
and overworked, you know?

838
00:33:57,393 --> 00:33:58,920
Could have been
a lot worse.

839
00:33:59,091 --> 00:34:00,885
You know, at least you didn't
leave it inside a patient.

840
00:34:00,972 --> 00:34:02,755
Yeah, well,
now it's inside our child.

841
00:34:04,642 --> 00:34:07,756
Teddy, I shouldn't have given
you the ring in the first place.

842
00:34:07,853 --> 00:34:09,287
You're a trauma surgeon.

843
00:34:09,383 --> 00:34:11,716
No, but I-I want
to wear the ring.

844
00:34:11,804 --> 00:34:13,097
I love the ring.

845
00:34:13,185 --> 00:34:14,185
And...

846
00:34:14,299 --> 00:34:16,131
And I-I love you.

847
00:34:18,553 --> 00:34:19,943
Okay.

848
00:34:20,031 --> 00:34:21,195
- You have a necklace.
- Mm-hmm.

849
00:34:21,282 --> 00:34:23,945
And you have an A for Allison
and an I for Leo.

850
00:34:24,033 --> 00:34:26,201
How about
we add a T and an O

851
00:34:26,334 --> 00:34:29,107
and you can wear your entire
family around your neck?

852
00:34:29,489 --> 00:34:30,496
Okay?

853
00:34:30,823 --> 00:34:33,146
And we're gonna
keep that ring in a safe

854
00:34:33,234 --> 00:34:35,232
for special occasions,
okay?

855
00:34:36,175 --> 00:34:38,287
I have never
loved you more.

856
00:34:44,247 --> 00:34:45,345
Do you smell that?

857
00:34:45,433 --> 00:34:46,593
Mm-hmm.

858
00:34:48,411 --> 00:34:49,661
Okay.

859
00:34:51,473 --> 00:34:52,506
Rock...

860
00:34:52,593 --> 00:34:54,506
You know what? I got it.
This one's on me.

861
00:34:54,834 --> 00:34:56,404
- You sure?
- Mm-hmm.

862
00:34:56,492 --> 00:34:58,615
- 'Cause it's...
- I know. Go.

863
00:34:58,703 --> 00:35:00,306
Let's do this.

864
00:35:07,508 --> 00:35:09,406
Kai's condition
was too advanced

865
00:35:09,494 --> 00:35:11,224
to successfully coil
the bleeding vessel,

866
00:35:11,348 --> 00:35:14,308
so we had to open him up,
do the partial lung resection.

867
00:35:16,315 --> 00:35:18,058
It's going to be
a difficult recovery.

868
00:35:18,364 --> 00:35:19,912
In time, he will
be able to swim,

869
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:22,678
but not competitively,
I'm afraid.

870
00:35:23,762 --> 00:35:25,193
That stuff...

871
00:35:25,720 --> 00:35:27,923
It's flavored
like French toast, right?

872
00:35:28,185 --> 00:35:29,306
Mm-hmm.

873
00:35:29,393 --> 00:35:31,592
I always smell
French toast.

874
00:35:32,162 --> 00:35:34,005
I feel like an idiot
I didn't know.

875
00:35:34,093 --> 00:35:35,443
They're targeting kids.

876
00:35:35,740 --> 00:35:39,676
It's flavored like cotton candy
and bubble gum, as well.

877
00:35:40,037 --> 00:35:41,506
You're not an idiot.

878
00:35:41,857 --> 00:35:43,143
They're evil.

879
00:35:46,104 --> 00:35:48,310
Thank you
for saving my son.

880
00:35:55,012 --> 00:35:56,865
Don't worry.
I won't rub it in.

881
00:35:57,418 --> 00:35:58,623
I'm sorry.

882
00:35:59,976 --> 00:36:02,479
Listen, when I was
on the other side of this,

883
00:36:02,567 --> 00:36:03,980
Yang drove me mad.

884
00:36:04,068 --> 00:36:07,217
She'd leave me notes all over
the place every day for months.

885
00:36:07,305 --> 00:36:08,834
"I was right.
You were wrong."

886
00:36:09,018 --> 00:36:11,092
Little pictures
of resected lungs.

887
00:36:11,513 --> 00:36:12,933
Well,
sounds about right.

888
00:36:14,396 --> 00:36:15,732
Wait, you know her?

889
00:36:17,652 --> 00:36:18,928
I, um...

890
00:36:19,016 --> 00:36:20,107
W...

891
00:36:20,381 --> 00:36:22,529
Um... I gotta go.

892
00:36:22,617 --> 00:36:25,670
<i>Most patients put off
facing the truth as long as possible.</i>

893
00:36:26,068 --> 00:36:27,201
<i>And we get it.</i>

894
00:36:27,321 --> 00:36:28,644
<i>We do it, too.</i>

895
00:36:28,919 --> 00:36:30,232
<i>We ignore things.</i>

896
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:31,717
<i>We stay under the covers.</i>

897
00:36:31,894 --> 00:36:33,435
<i>We don't pick up
the phone.</i>

898
00:36:33,719 --> 00:36:36,372
Ah. I thought you'd have
some work to catch up on.

899
00:36:36,460 --> 00:36:38,263
You... You probably need
to do some unpacking,

900
00:36:38,351 --> 00:36:40,490
shake the sand out from
the beach, do some laundry...

901
00:36:40,643 --> 00:36:42,560
I wasn't on vacation,
Tom.

902
00:36:42,693 --> 00:36:44,928
I sat in my house
for three days.

903
00:36:45,016 --> 00:36:47,505
I didn't get out of bed,
I drank chamomile tea,

904
00:36:47,593 --> 00:36:51,056
and I cried my eyes out
because I had a miscarriage.

905
00:36:51,467 --> 00:36:54,386
That happened,
I'm sad about it,

906
00:36:54,560 --> 00:36:55,769
and I'm taking care
of myself.

907
00:36:55,857 --> 00:36:56,894
Any questions?

908
00:36:56,982 --> 00:36:59,053
- You could have told me.
- I just did.

909
00:36:59,796 --> 00:37:01,049
W... Light a candle.

910
00:37:01,506 --> 00:37:02,576
What?

911
00:37:02,751 --> 00:37:05,204
When my wife...
Uh, my ex-wife, uh, Dana...

912
00:37:05,299 --> 00:37:08,372
She miscarried twice
before we had David.

913
00:37:08,460 --> 00:37:12,173
Once at 10 weeks,
once at 18, which was...

914
00:37:12,353 --> 00:37:14,428
Well, I mean, you know...
You know how it was.

915
00:37:14,516 --> 00:37:16,839
I mean, people have
this idea that, uh...

916
00:37:17,076 --> 00:37:18,123
you just get over it,

917
00:37:18,211 --> 00:37:21,874
that, uh, you know,
you're sad and you move on.

918
00:37:21,962 --> 00:37:25,473
But... that wasn't
my experience.

919
00:37:25,784 --> 00:37:27,949
Wasn't
my wife's experience.

920
00:37:28,113 --> 00:37:29,957
So every year, still,

921
00:37:30,183 --> 00:37:32,528
uh, on what would be
their birthdays,

922
00:37:32,699 --> 00:37:35,856
I, uh,
I light a candle.

923
00:37:36,269 --> 00:37:40,176
They took with them
little pieces of our... hearts,

924
00:37:40,598 --> 00:37:42,746
and those pieces
will never be...

925
00:37:43,472 --> 00:37:45,035
replaced.

926
00:37:46,708 --> 00:37:48,621
So, maybe, uh...

927
00:37:49,257 --> 00:37:50,582
light a candle.

928
00:37:52,574 --> 00:37:53,947
Yeah.

929
00:38:01,643 --> 00:38:04,567
<i>We don't face the music
and all that crap.</i>

930
00:38:04,880 --> 00:38:08,333
<i>♪ Mamma,
you have shown me love ♪</i>

931
00:38:08,458 --> 00:38:11,113
You paged me
to the plant room.

932
00:38:13,013 --> 00:38:14,466
Never a good sign.

933
00:38:18,004 --> 00:38:19,770
When someone shows you
who they are,

934
00:38:19,858 --> 00:38:21,434
you're supposed to
believe them.

935
00:38:23,371 --> 00:38:26,348
Someone said that today,
and it... it kinda hit me.

936
00:38:28,933 --> 00:38:31,096
We're doctors.

937
00:38:31,183 --> 00:38:32,972
There are tests.

938
00:38:33,667 --> 00:38:36,636
If there was a question
who the father was,

939
00:38:36,755 --> 00:38:39,048
I should have known that
from the beginning.

940
00:38:39,347 --> 00:38:40,550
You're right.

941
00:38:40,836 --> 00:38:42,948
I'm not always...

942
00:38:43,856 --> 00:38:45,106
measured.

943
00:38:45,871 --> 00:38:49,417
I'm not ever
measured.

944
00:38:51,367 --> 00:38:53,167
I'm a little bit chaotic.

945
00:38:54,033 --> 00:38:55,885
I fly
by the seat of my pants,

946
00:38:55,973 --> 00:38:58,716
and I... don't think things
all the way through,

947
00:38:58,803 --> 00:39:00,652
and...

948
00:39:01,378 --> 00:39:03,293
..sometimes
that hurts people.

949
00:39:05,534 --> 00:39:07,394
I'm sorry
that I hurt you.

950
00:39:09,105 --> 00:39:11,941
<i>♪ Nothing here
could block your truth ♪</i>

951
00:39:12,055 --> 00:39:14,902
There are a bunch of people
involved in this.

952
00:39:15,723 --> 00:39:17,473
And they deserve to know.

953
00:39:20,391 --> 00:39:22,160
I deserve to know.

954
00:39:22,248 --> 00:39:26,433
<i>♪ I'm captured
by the good you do ♪</i>

955
00:39:26,745 --> 00:39:28,957
And if we do
find out...

956
00:39:30,385 --> 00:39:32,308
that you're not
the father?

957
00:39:33,393 --> 00:39:36,574
I want to be the guy that says,
uh, it doesn't matter,

958
00:39:36,763 --> 00:39:38,192
but I don't know yet.

959
00:39:38,754 --> 00:39:40,606
I don't know
how much it matters.

960
00:39:41,213 --> 00:39:43,622
I guess...
I-I think we should...

961
00:39:44,776 --> 00:39:47,689
take it
one step at a time.

962
00:39:48,419 --> 00:39:50,216
Gather information.

963
00:39:57,019 --> 00:40:00,352
So much for me
never making you cry.

964
00:40:00,848 --> 00:40:04,317
<i>But the longer we hide,
the worse it can be.</i>

965
00:40:05,567 --> 00:40:07,286
<i>So, open the test results.</i>

966
00:40:07,374 --> 00:40:08,377
Hey.

967
00:40:08,465 --> 00:40:09,805
Have the hard conversation.

968
00:40:09,893 --> 00:40:10,966
I got your text.

969
00:40:11,053 --> 00:40:12,636
Say what you mean.

970
00:40:12,723 --> 00:40:14,176
Hey, maybe
we should go to dinner

971
00:40:14,263 --> 00:40:15,459
and clear your head
a little bit.

972
00:40:15,546 --> 00:40:18,106
Her name's Suzanne,
she's got two young kids,

973
00:40:18,194 --> 00:40:20,357
she's a single mom,
and I think she's dying.

974
00:40:20,553 --> 00:40:22,122
Okay.
Are these from today?

975
00:40:22,210 --> 00:40:23,363
Yeah,
she crashed on me.

976
00:40:23,577 --> 00:40:26,370
I had to aspirate
a cardiac tamponade... in CT.

977
00:40:26,473 --> 00:40:27,544
I don't get it.

978
00:40:27,632 --> 00:40:29,255
It was a simple appy,
a no-brainer case,

979
00:40:29,343 --> 00:40:31,546
and... and now,
I mean, look at all this.

980
00:40:31,763 --> 00:40:33,559
She's...
She's getting worse.

981
00:40:33,647 --> 00:40:35,361
And I don't know why
or how to help her.

982
00:40:35,449 --> 00:40:38,431
Hey.
Andrew, look at me.

983
00:40:38,712 --> 00:40:40,853
Walk me through it.
From the beginning.

984
00:40:41,033 --> 00:40:42,744
- Good or bad...
- Okay.

985
00:40:43,270 --> 00:40:45,305
..you may be surprised
at what you find.

986
00:40:45,393 --> 00:40:46,636
You're right. Okay.

987
00:40:46,723 --> 00:40:48,716
She was post-op,
day three...

988
00:41:06,594 --> 00:41:08,417
<i>♪ Whoa, whoa ♪</i>

989
00:41:08,512 --> 00:41:10,135
<i>♪ Whoa, whoa ♪</i>

990
00:41:17,259 --> 00:41:19,895
<i>♪ Have no fear ♪</i>

991
00:41:20,073 --> 00:41:21,345
Oh.

992
00:41:21,447 --> 00:41:23,270
How was your day?

993
00:41:23,499 --> 00:41:25,275
Uh, uneventful.

994
00:41:28,231 --> 00:41:31,804
Dr. Wells from Pac-North called,
looking for you.

995
00:41:31,892 --> 00:41:34,228
Said you didn't go to work.

996
00:41:34,466 --> 00:41:35,799
I didn't.

997
00:41:35,973 --> 00:41:39,705
I was... trying to convince
Maggie to go back to work.

998
00:41:40,263 --> 00:41:42,165
And that took you
all day?

999
00:41:42,613 --> 00:41:43,798
Yes.

1000
00:41:43,886 --> 00:41:45,994
<i>♪ Have no fear ♪</i>

1001
00:41:46,138 --> 00:41:48,736
Catherine, this isn't gonna work
if you don't trust me.

1002
00:41:50,665 --> 00:41:52,408
Who said this is working?

1003
00:41:56,456 --> 00:41:58,197
Well,
what are you saying?

1004
00:41:59,775 --> 00:42:01,337
Richard...

1005
00:42:01,649 --> 00:42:03,095
I think it's time for us

1006
00:42:03,183 --> 00:42:06,048
to have
a much bigger conversation.

1007
00:42:09,050 --> 00:42:10,633
<i>♪ Beloved ain't enough ♪</i>

1008
00:42:10,721 --> 00:42:12,504
<i>And at the very least,</i>

1009
00:42:12,597 --> 00:42:14,572
<i>you'll know
